    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-03-19T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-03-19T09:00:00-05:00" n="106"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d106">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72119/1477</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-03-19T14:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 19, 1918, 2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 2.11 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>9116. Your 6912, March 16, 5 p.m.<note n="4" xml:id="d106fn4">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_154">p. 154</ref>.</note>
                    Inter-Allied Socialist Conference in resolution, forwarded to Department in my
                    despatch No. 8522, March 11,<note n="5" xml:id="d106fn5">Not printed.</note>
                    provided that international conference shall be held in some neutral country
                    organized by committee of neutral Socialists and attended by full representation
                    of Socialists from belligerent countries. <persName corresp="#p_HA1"
                        >Henderson</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_HC2">Huysmans</persName>
                    state that no such international conference could be held if German Socialists
                    were absent, or even if Minority German Socialists were not represented.
                        <persName corresp="#p_HA1">Henderson</persName> says the Prime Minister told
                    him in December that British Socialists would be allowed to proceed to such a
                    conference only in case German Government allowed that the conference to [<hi
                        rend="italic">should</hi>] be attended by both Minority and Majority German
                        <pb facs="0261" n="169" xml:id="pg_169"/> Socialists. No secret proposal was
                    submitted to recent conference by either <persName corresp="#p_TA1">Albert
                        Thomas</persName> of France or <persName>J. H. Thomas</persName> of England.
                        <persName corresp="#p_HA1">Henderson</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_HC2">Huysmans</persName> both state that they would certainly
                    have seen such a secret document had it existed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PWH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
